RequiredLevel=11
PosMap=36

[QUEST203]
Nombre=Humans, a while ago
Desc=Around Nix, some Human forms prowl, it is said that they used to be fishermen from the area... if you manage to clear the Graveyard of these creatures, I will reward you!
DescFinal=Great job!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=11
PosMap=36

[QUEST204]
Nombre=Winds of Eldoria
Desc=Great warrior, welcome to the lands of Eldoria! Exotic creatures of incalculable power lurk near this village. I've tried to approach, but a Guardian Spirit is preventing me. If you dare to defeat them and obtain the Wind Rune for me, I will reward you with a great spell.
DescFinal=You're back! Many have fallen by the wayside, unable to help me. I appreciate your bravery. Take this wind rune and use it on your adventure!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=29
PosMap=123

[QUEST206]
Nombre=Blood for Blood
Desc=I've discovered a way to enhance the Summon Piranha spell, but I need the wild essence drawn directly from their carnivorous counterparts. Travel south of this city and eliminate the piranhas dominating the current. Draw on their essence to fuel the spell... and prove yourself worthy of harnessing their fury.
DescFinal=With this spell, you'll be able to defend yourself from any threat on the high seas!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
PosMap=78

[QUEST207]
Nombre=Evil Awakens
Desc=Dravonius appears to be an immortal Demon, but by fighting tirelessly against him, we can weaken his influence. There is ancient knowledge, hidden from most, that could give you an advantage. Some whisper that forgotten texts lie beneath sacred ground… but I can say nothing more.
DescFinal=Excellent battle, Dravonius' influence is weakening!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=20

[QUEST208]
Nombre=Profane relic
Desc=Codex Daemonicarum – Tiberius Marcellan: "When Rangue, lord of deception, created Dravonius in the darkness, he did not do so naked. He covered his body with a cloak crafted from all the lies he ever told his victims, a cloth that absorbs the light and hope of those who behold it. Much of his strength seems to come from this, this tireless ability of the daemon and its tenacity to re-take bodies. No one has ever been able to remove this profane garment, a relic of the underworld, and discover his true power. He who wears it covers not only his flesh, but his soul: the Daemon's Cloak."
DescFinal=This holy place removed all curses from the Mantle, wear it carefully.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=20

[QUEST209]
Nombre=Hand over the letter.
Desc=I have heard the murmur of your path... voices of swamps, echoes of steel, footsteps taken between shadows and flames. You represent neither light nor night. Not yet. That is why I can speak to you without judgment. (Aduin observes the letter you hand him and turns his gaze toward the coast) These lands need silence to hear the deep.
DescFinal=Many wield steel, but few understand the weight of an action. You carry something different. It's not just strength... it's purpose, even if you don't fully understand it yet.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST210]
Nombre=Reduce their forces.
Desc=Listen carefully: I am a spy, not a warrior. My job is to observe, listen, and survive. But you... you are hardened iron, hardened in battle. You must enter the Arkhein Drain. There, enemy guards are gathering to march toward the Har Nareth Refuge, where they are preparing for a confrontation. Your mission: reduce their numbers before they can reinforce that position. The chaos you create down there will slow their movements... and that will give us the advantage. When you have reduced enough guards, return to me.
DescFinal=Impressive. I didn't think you'd manage it so effectively.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST211]
Nombre=Reduce their forces.
Desc=Listen. I am eyes, a voice in whispers... but not a sword. My duty is to remain invisible, not to unleash the carnage this war demands. You must infiltrate the Banderbill Drain. Beneath those luminous streets, Navy soldiers are preparing a raid on a key territory within the drain. Your task is simple in words, brutal in deed: eliminate them. Let the blood be silent, but not abundant. Return when the work is done. I will be watching, as always.
DescFinal=Magnificent. The Banderbill drainage system is still trembling from your presence.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST212]
Nombre=Royal Exchange
Desc=Wow... so you made it. I didn't expect you to arrive with the Tome of Wisdom intact. Only a few survive the journey to Arkhein without losing it... or losing themselves.
DescFinal=Kael extends his hand and takes the Tome with restrained reverence.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST213]
Nombre=Legionary Exchange
Desc=Ah… vous avez donc survécu jusqu’ici. Et le Tome de l’Expertise est toujours entre vos mains… admirable. La plupart tombent avant même de franchir la première ligne de patrouille.
DescFinal=Serik picks up the Tome with careful, almost ceremonial fingers.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST214]
Nombre=The meeting with Kael
Desc=Congratulations. The leader of the Royal Navy has placed his trust in you and entrusted you with the Royal Scroll. Take this Tome of Wisdom, an essential relic for the responsibility that lies ahead. Your task is simple in its necessity and perilous in its execution: travel to the enemy city of Arkhein and locate the undercover agent known as "Kael Shadowlive." Deliver the Tome and assist him in incorporating classified information that only he possesses. Be aware: in Arkhein, the guards act without mercy. Attempt to infiltrate using all your strength or call for assistance: if you are discovered, defense will be your only option. Guard the Tome with utmost care: its loss would be irreparable for our cause.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST215]
Nombre=The meeting with Serik
Desc=So be it. The leader of the Dark Legion has considered your request and entrusted you with the Legionary Scroll. Take this Tome of Expertise, a relic forged from forbidden knowledge and the memory of war. You must carry it now to the enemy city of Banderbill, lair of the weak who still cling to the light. There, seek out the infiltrator operating under the name of Serik the Veil. Deliver the Tome so that he may add the information only he possesses. But listen carefully: the guards of Banderbill will attack without warning, without hesitation, and without mercy. Protect the Tome with your life. To lose it would mean not only your failure, but your extinction as a Legion aspirant.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST216]
Nombre=Restore your Honor
Desc=Citizen, my name is Tharion, Justice of the Crown. I come to offer you a chance to redeem your tainted soul. Take to the battlefield and strike down the guardians of the Dark Legion. Only by facing the shadow can you regain the light of your honor and once again proudly serve this Kingdom.
DescFinal=You have cleared your name with honor. The Kingdom trusts that you will continue to serve with valor.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST217]
Nombre=Blood for Redemption
Desc=My name is Vhortenak, I have come to clear your name before the Legion. If you wish to return to the ranks of Chaos, you must stain your hands once more. Slay the Royal Navy guards and offer their blood as proof of loyalty. Forgiveness, in these lands, is earned with death!
DescFinal=You have demonstrated loyalty in the blood shed. Forgiveness begins to open for you. May the shadows guide you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST218]
Nombre=Introduction to Blacksmithing
Desc=As workers, one of our great gifts is Mining. Grab a pickaxe and head to the Iron Mines east of Nix and get me about 100 Ingots, the King has requested that we make more weapons for his troops and this will be enough to create several swords. But be careful, there are some fighters in the mines who will seek to take your resources.
DescFinal=Sweat pays with a good reward, take this.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=34

[QUEST219]
Nombre=Introduction to Carpentry
Desc=We can always demonstrate our strength against natural forces, but we can also use its resources to create ships, crafts, and even bows. Grab a Lumberjack Axe, head into the forest to get 500 Logs and craft 10 Wooden Spoons. The town cook plans to feed the beggars!
DescFinal=The town will appreciate your cooperation, I will send these resources to the cook immediately.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=14
PosMap=78

[QUEST220]
Nombre=Legionary strength coat
Desc=I can forge a shield for you, it will be worthy of the forces of chaos.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=40

[QUEST222]
Nombre=1kk
Desc=Give me 1 gold coin and I will give you 1kk of exp
DescFinal=Thanks for the currency, even if it doesn't reach me at all.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=1
PosMap=1

[QUEST223]
Nombre=Level 12
Desc=Give me 12 gold coins and I'll make you level 12
DescFinal=Thank you, you could have been a bit more generous.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1
PosMap=34

[QUEST224]
Nombre=Apprentice Scramer
Desc=Defeat 20 Scramers and speak to the Wise Old Man again to receive your reward.
DescFinal=You have brought peace to my home, this award is for you!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=5

[QUEST225]
Nombre=Adventurer Scramer
Desc=Defeat 40 Scramers and speak to the Wise Old Man again to receive your reward.
DescFinal=You have brought peace to my home, this award is for you!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=5

[QUEST226]
Nombre=Master Scramer
Desc=Defeat 80 Scramers and speak to the Wise Old Man again to receive your reward.
DescFinal=You have brought peace to my home, this award is for you!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=5

[QUEST227]
Nombre=White Poison
Desc=Clear the Island so Astrid can peacefully investigate the Light Mushrooms!
DescFinal=Thanks for your help, maybe these mushrooms will help you too.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=1

[QUEST230]
Nombre=The Roar of Bruin
Desc=That pelt you brought me... magnificent. But it is not enough to create what I have in mind. There is another Bear, one the hunters call Bruin, the Dark One. His strength is unmatched, and his fur is so thick that frost cracks at the touch. He lives in the Bear Woods, northeast of here. He does not always show himself... but when he roars, even the mountains tremble. If you truly desire a mount worthy of legend, bring me his pelt as a token of my courage. Only with its power can I forge the bond between Beast and Rider.
DescFinal=So you've done it... you've defeated Bruin. I can feel his strength, even through his skin. It's like holding winter's fury contained in a single piece. With this, and the silver hide you gave me earlier, the harness will be complete. But what you've gained goes beyond a mount: you've earned the respect of nature itself.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1

[QUEST231]
Nombre=The Needle and the Claw
Desc=Listen carefully, traveler. I seek a rare pelt, one not all eyes have been privileged to see. This is the Pelt of the Silver Brown Bear, a rarity among rarities; only a few are born under the light of the winter moon with that metallic sheen in their fur. With one of these pelts, I could create something unique: a harness and saddle so sturdy that not even the blizzards of Nix could break them.
DescFinal=Have you really achieved it? That texture, that shine… unmistakable.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1

[QUEST232]
Nombre=Lynn's Blood
Desc=If you have the courage to enter the Cave of the Nagas and extract a sample of their Blood, and also bring me a special potion, you will be rewarded with great power.
DescFinal=Great job, with this Flash you'll have incredible power!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=27
PosMap=517

[QUEST233]
Nombre=Fiery Heart of the Leviathan
Desc=At north of this abandoned city lies the most dangerous creature in the sea. Few sorcerers have the courage to face it, but if you prove otherwise, manage to defeat it and tear out its Heart, I can grant you an upgrade to your Blazing Flare.
DescFinal=Great work, get your reward!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
PosMap=171

[QUEST234]
Nombre=The power of Magic
Desc=Being a Great Wizard is not just about casting spells, you must be able to concentrate your mana and be able to channel it correctly. Demonstrate your power to the goblin colony in the forest north of Ullathrope and I will prepare you for your next adventures.
DescFinal=You've done it! Have this Apprentice's Staff as a reward.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST235]
Nombre=Nature calls
Desc=As druids, our power comes from the essence of Nature. In order to become a great druid you must be able to understand the balance between our power and the creatures of the world around us. Eliminate the wolf pack from North-west Ullathorpe and I will give you tools to increase your power.
DescFinal=Nature appreciates your control in the world, but remember that without it we are nothing. This Apprentice Flute should help you for your next adventure.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST236]
Nombre=The light of rhythm
Desc=Music brings us power, but we must know how to play the right melody. Practice your Bardic power on the skeletons south of Banderbill Jail and bring me one of their skulls. May the music shake your bones!
DescFinal=Now do you understand the power that music gives us? Have this Apprentice Lute, you will be amazing one day!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST237]
Nombre=The Kingdom of Shadows
Desc=The shadows are our ally, your dagger and your hands must be one. Return the Lesser Liches to the grave where they belong, and bring back their treasure. Doing so will equip you for your next adventure.
DescFinal=The magic of Shadows strengthens us! Have this Apprentice Dagger, it will help you destroy your victims.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST238]
Nombre=The strength of Faith
Desc=As Clergy, we must learn to concentrate our Faith, it is the force that moves us. The shadows have stirred up some wild wolves. Annihilate the evil that stalks them and exorcise their bodies.
DescFinal=At last the forest will be able to rest in peace. Take this Apprentice Sword, it will help you on your adventures!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST239]
Nombre=Stroke of luck
Desc=You could say that luck runs through our veins. There is a group of newbies who call themselves ?Bandits? and they have been robbing merchants south of Banderbill, they are just dedicated to tarnishing our name. Beat them up and I'll reward you.
DescFinal=Luck is on your side! Have these Apprentice Knuckles to improve your critical hits.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST240]
Nombre=Necessary purification
Desc=Our job as Paladins is to purify this world of shadows. We have received information about a horde of Zombies east of Ullathorpe. Cleanse these lands of evil and I will equip you for your next crusade.
DescFinal=The earth is a little cleaner with your help. Take this Apprentice Sword, noble Paladin!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST241]
Nombre=Brute Force
Desc=We are the most resilient beings in the world, we do not require that stupid magic to destroy our enemies. I have heard that the Gray Vulpes have reproduced and have started to be a problem. You can find them west of Ullathorpe, kill them and I will give you an unmatched weapon.
DescFinal=Your weapon and your body are one, take this Apprentice Sword for your next adventure.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST242]
Nombre=Target Shooting
Desc=You and your bow must be one and the same. To the west of the city of Penthar you will find a perfect place to practice your aim. Eliminate some Orcs from that area and I will give you something to help you in your next hunts.
DescFinal=I can see that your bow and arrows never fail! This Apprentice Bow should help you on your next hunt.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=7
PosMap=264

[QUEST243]
Nombre=The Howl in the Gloom
Desc=Wild Wolves prowl our lands under the shadow of a sick moon. The weapons master summons you: you must not only hunt them, but also pluck from one of them its Cursed Fang. Only a wolf, touched by darkness, bears it. Seek, wait
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1
Descfinal=¡Gran trabajo derrotando al Triturador, pero debes volver al norte, la ciudad aun te necesita!
DescFinal=You've done it! That tusk isn't obtained without courage. Take it to Bertrand, the famous Blacksmith of Nix; he may have a weapon for you.

[QUEST244]
Nombre=prueba
Desc=You must stop the Spider Queen's attack! If you manage to defeat one of her protectors, the Spider Anomaly, you will go down in this town's history!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1
Descfinal=¡Gran trabajo derrotando a la Anomalía, pero debes volver al norte, la ciudad aun te necesita!
DescFinal=Great job defeating the Anomaly, but you need to head back north, the city still needs you!

[QUEST245]
Nombre=Arachnid Spellcaster
Desc=You must stop the Spider Queen's attack! If you manage to defeat one of her protectors, the Spider-Wizard, you will go down in this town's history!
DescFinal=Great job defeating the Sorcerer, but you must return north, the city still needs you!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1

[QUEST246]
Nombre=Arachnid Queen
Desc=The last effort to defend this city... If you manage to defeat Ghulvara, the Spider Queen, you will be worthy of this recognition!
DescFinal=You've done it, this story is finally over... the peace of Ullathorpe City is restored, and you will go down in the history of this game... Have this Spider Mutant Reins as recognition of your bravery!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1

[QUEST247]
Nombre=Level 24
Desc=Give me 24 gold coins and I'll make you level 24
DescFinal=Thank you, you could have been a bit more generous.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=1
PosMap=34
DescAudio=1109
DescFinalAudio=1110

[QUEST248]
Nombre=Poison Potions
Desc=You now have a basic understanding of Alchemy. If you want to acquire the skill of creating Poison Potions, you'll need to complete the following quest.
DescFinal=Great Job! Here you have your recipe, Now you can create strength potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=18

[QUEST249]
Nombre=The Fire of the Ancient
Desc=You have come a long way to find me here in Kamal. My name is Vulkano, master of the Ancient Fire. I have aided the greatest sorcerers of this world, but I no longer grant power freely. To prove you are worthy of this knowledge, you must enter the Dragon’s Lair and retrieve 1 Fire Rune. If you succeed, you shall be rewarded.
DescFinal=Few have faced such fury and lived to tell the tale. You are worthy. Watch and learn... this is the ancient spell of the Fire Elementals. From now on, fire answers your call. Use it wisely... or be consumed by it.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=31
PosMap=17

[QUEST250]
Nombre=Antidotote recipe
Desc=You can now create Life and Mana potions, if you want to acquire the ability to create Antidotes, you will have to complete the following mission!
DescFinal=Great job! Here you have your Recipe, now you can create Antidotes.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=10
PosMap=561

[QUEST251]
Nombre=Life potions
Desc=Pay close attention: to acquire the ability to create Life potions, you will have to complete the following mission!
DescFinal=Great job, here is your recipe, now you can create Life Potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=6
PosMap=561

[QUEST252]
Nombre=Maná potions
Desc=You can now create Life potions, if you want to acquire the ability to create MANA potions, you will have to complete the following mission!
DescFinal=Great job! Here you have your Recipe, now you can create Mana Potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=8
PosMap=561

[QUEST253]
Nombre=Potions of strength
Desc=You Can Now Create Life, Mana, Antidotes, Energy and Agility Potions. If you want to acquire the ability to create strength potions, you will have to complete the following quest!
DescFinal=Great Job! Here you have your recipe, Now you can create strength potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=16
PosMap=561

[QUEST254]
Nombre=Agility potions
Desc=You can now create Life, Mana, Antidotes and Energy potions. If you want to acquire the ability to create Agility potions, you will have to complete the following quest!
DescFinal=Great job! Here you have your Recipe, now you can create Agility Potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=14
PosMap=561

[QUEST255]
Nombre=Potions of energy
Desc=You can now create potions of Life, Mana and Antidotes. If you want to acquire the ability to create Energy potions, you will have to complete the following quest!
DescFinal=Great job! Here you have your Recipe, now you can create Energy Potions.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=12
PosMap=561

[QUEST256]
Nombre=Level 1 Rider
Desc=Welcome to my Stable. With this series of assignments I've prepared for your entire career, you can become what I once was. To obtain your first Rider level, you must head to the Mines of Doom and extract a Mysterious Fluid from one of the Dactyls. Stay alert; don't underestimate its power.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 15.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=10
PosMap=188

[QUEST257]
Nombre=Level 2 Rider
Desc=This second quest requires you to approach the entrance to the dreaded Marabel Dungeon. If you manage to clear the entrance, obtain an Orc Axe, and return alive, you will be rewarded.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 20.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=15
PosMap=188

[QUEST258]
Nombre=Level 3 Rider
Desc=Only adventurers of Level 20 or higher may accept this perilous mission. Within the Dragon Dungeon, an ancient creature lurks in the shadows. The Beholder's gaze can disintegrate the weak and break the minds of the brave. Your objective is clear: remove the Central Eye of the Beholder and bring it back as irrefutable proof of your bravery.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 25.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=20
PosMap=188

[QUEST259]
Nombre=Level 4 Rider
Desc=The Minions have desecrated the Forsaken Lair, an ancient refuge now corrupted by dark energies. Deep within, they have forged a Daemon Stone, a source of evil power that threatens to unleash chaos beyond its walls. Your mission is clear: enter the Lair, eliminate all the Minions in your path, and retrieve the Daemon Stone before its power spreads. Return with it, and you will be rewarded as a true hero.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 30.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
PosMap=188

[QUEST260]
Nombre=Level 5 Rider
Desc=An ice golem has sacked the Village of Eleuria, stealing the sacred Polar Pendant from an Ancient Guardian. The relic keeps the bitter cold at bay. Travel to the Glacier Cave, confront the fearsome creature, and retrieve it. Only those wearing Winter Robes can survive the icy descent and fulfill this ancient duty.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 35.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=30
PosMap=188

[QUEST261]
Nombre=Level 6 Rider
Desc=The depths of Dungeon Verill have been corrupted by arcane entities. Eliminating 100 Medusae and 50 Witches is required to restore balance. Among the remains may be the Codex Umbrarum Verill, a forbidden manuscript that holds ancient secrets about the creation and curse of the place. Only the worthy may unravel its hidden knowledge.
DescFinal=Great job! Here's this consumable, come back and see me when you're Level 40.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=35
PosMap=188

[QUEST262]
Nombre=Level 7 Rider
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=40

[QUEST263]
Nombre=Level 8 Rider
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=45

[QUEST264]
Nombre=Level 9 Rider
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=47

[QUEST265]
Nombre=Mule Exchange
Desc=If you previously obtained the Mule, accept this Quest and I will reward you with the equivalent Consumable.
DescFinal=You may consume the item I offer you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=20

[QUEST266]
Nombre=Brown Horse Exchange
Desc=If you previously obtained the Brown Horse, accept this Quest and I will reward you with the equivalent Consumable.
DescFinal=You may consume the item I offer you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=24

[QUEST267]
Nombre=White Horse Exchange
Desc=If you previously obtained the White Horse, accept this Quest and I will reward you with the equivalent Consumable.
DescFinal=You may consume the item I offer you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=28

[QUEST268]
Nombre=Fighter Mount Exchange
Desc=If you have previously obtained the Fighter's Mount, accept this Quest and I will reward you with the equivalent Consumable.
DescFinal=You may consume the item I offer you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=32

[QUEST269]
Nombre=Palomino Horse Exchange
Desc=If you previously obtained the Palomino Horse, accept this Quest and I will reward you with the equivalent Consumable.
DescFinal=You may consume the item I offer you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=36

[QUEST270]
Nombre=The Legacy of Shadows
Desc=The 9 Primordial Stones, scattered across the world and guarded by fearsome guardians, must be reunited to prevent dark forces from unleashing chaos. The last vestige of the sages has fallen into the hands of those who do not understand the power they seek. Now, only you can restore balance or succumb to the abyss.
DescFinal=You have completed the task many have deemed impossible. The 9 Stones are now reunited, and with them, the Chest of the Dark Legacy. Beware, traveler. The power you have unleashed cannot be undone. The fate of the world, at last, rests in your hands.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=35
PosMap=171

[QUEST271]
Nombre=Key Exchange for Armor
Desc=If you have obtained the Darkness Key, claim this quest to obtain your Armor
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=35

[QUEST272]
Nombre=Key Exchange for Robe
Desc=If you have obtained the Darkness Key, claim this quest to obtain your Robe.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=35

[QUEST273]
Nombre=To get the scale.
Desc=With that advantage, the next move has arrived. Deep within the Drainage, where mud mingles with ancient echoes, a creature feared even by its own kind often manifests: the Har Nareth. A colossal beast, half reptile, half something else... something nature would rather forget. Sometimes it appears... sometimes it doesn't. Its presence is capricious, like death itself patiently waiting. If you have the strength, you could try to face it alone. If not... gather allies who aren't afraid to scream among the tunnels. When it falls, take a scale from its body. Just one. It will be more than enough.
DescFinal=Now you must travel to the Isle of Griffins. Among crags and wind, you will find Aduin the Wanderer. He belongs neither to the Crown nor to the Shades; he is a sage who lives observing the world without taking sides. Take this letter to him as soon as possible.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST274]
Nombre=To get the scale.
Desc=This imbalance works in our favor, and now we can move into the crucial phase. In the heart of the Drain, where the darkness is so thick it chills you to the bone, the Har Nareth appears from time to time. An immense beast with the strength of ancient swamps and the fury of what should never have existed. Sometimes it rests there, other times it hunts. You never know when the beast will reveal itself. You may be able to face it alone, or you may need hands that aren't afraid of breaking. Choose wisely. If it falls before you, pluck a scale from its body. Just one. We need it.
DescFinal=Now you must travel to the Isle of Griffins. Among crags and wind, you will find Aduin the Wanderer. He belongs neither to the Crown nor to the Shades; he is a sage who lives observing the world without taking sides. Take this letter to him as soon as possible.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST275]
Nombre=Dagger Poison
Desc=The Abandoned Lair is no longer empty. Corrupted gargoyles cling to its ruins, creatures of stone and poison whose touch infects flesh. A single blow is enough to feel the acid coursing through your veins. From their bodies, Acid Fluid can be extracted, a volatile and extremely dangerous substance. It is the key ingredient in a forbidden art: Toxin Edge. Bring me that fluid, and I will teach you how to poison your daggers like a true assassin. But keep your cool… the gargoyles sense weakness. If fear takes hold, you will not leave the lair.
DescFinal=From now on, your blades will drink poison with every strike. This is the Toxin Edge... Use it wisely, or die by your own hand.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
PosMap=560

[QUEST276]
Nombre=Recover the Slope
Desc=The Pendant of Omens is more valuable than any weapon or gem. It belongs to no flag... and yet, both kings would covet it. Within it lies an ancient symbol, a sign that can open doors that cannot be forced open. Unfortunately, one of those eagles managed to snatch it from me. You must retrieve it, as soon as possible.
DescFinal=Listen carefully: this object must not be lost. Nor forgotten. Nor exchanged. You must return to your capital city... there they will understand the significance of what you now carry.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST277]
Nombre=The Renaissance
Desc=By the skies of the Crown... the rumors of your feat are true. That pendant has passed through the hands of kings, knights errant, and sages who guided entire ages. Its worth is not measured in gold, steel, or blood, but in history and destiny. You have walked the Path. You have shown mettle, sacrifice, and purpose. Nothing more remains to be proven. (Tharion extends his hand, revealing a polished, translucent gem, charged with light.) Receive now the Gem of Factional Pardon. It is your key. Your symbol. Your rebirth. Guard it as you guard your honor. Once presented to the Court, your name may once more echo beneath the banner of the Empire.
DescFinal=You have returned... not as a supplicant, but as one worthy. May the Light guide you.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST278]
Nombre=The Claim
Desc=For generations this symbol has not pierced these shadows. It belongs not to kings, nor to temples... but to those capable of bending their own destiny. You have survived swamps, sewers, ancient beasts, and mind-breaking silences. Not through obedience, but through determination. Take the Factional Forgiveness Gem. It represents not absolution... but retribution.
DescFinal=Keep it. Hide it. Protect it. When the time comes, hand it over, and your name will once again be whispered among the ranks of the Legion.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST279]
Nombre=Learn the recipe for Fire
Desc=Thirga Brumhilda has entrusted you with a burning task. Within the portal to the Forest of Spirits, the Firebearers guard ancient pages of a lost grimoire. Gather 50 Book of Fire Pages, forged in the very heat of creation. Only then will you be able to master the Recipe of the Element of Fire, symbol of the power and passion of the dwarven forge.
DescFinal=Ha! I can smell the smoke on your clothes and see the fire's gleam in your eyes. You have brought the burning blades, and with them, the knowledge of the ancient smiths. From this day forward, fire will answer your hammer. Use this recipe with pride, Worker, and let every blow ignite Morgrim's story!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=28
PosMap=594

[QUEST280]
Nombre=Learn the recipe for Water
Desc=Thirga has spoken to you of the balance of Water, a patient and malleable element. In the Ancestral Vision, the Water Bearers protect the pages of a fluid and ever-changing grimoire. Gather 50 Water Book Pages and prove that you can temper your will like steel beneath the stream. Master the Recipe of the Water Element and let serenity guide your hand.
DescFinal=I see you've learned the lesson of water... patient, constant, unbreakable. Water polishes stone like work polishes a dwarf. Take this recipe and let it flow in your forge. May every drop that falls on the metal remind you who you are.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=28
PosMap=594

[QUEST281]
Nombre=Learn the recipe for Wind
Desc=In the Ancestral Vision, Windbearers move amidst invisible gusts, safeguarding volatile power. Thirga Brumhilda challenges you to collect 50 Wind Book Leaves, fragments as light and elusive as a current of air. Only those who understand the freedom of the wind can master the Wind Element Recipe.
DescFinal=You moved swiftly, like a stream through the mountains. The wind is not easily captured, but you have tamed it with your effort. Receive this recipe, and let the breath of the air bless your forges. No wall can contain a free spirit.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=28
PosMap=594

[QUEST282]
Nombre=Learn the recipe for Earth
Desc=Thirga's final challenge leads you to the Earth Bearers. Their leaves weigh as much as mountains, and only a truly persevering worker can gather 50 Earth Book Leaves. The Earth Element Recipe represents the stability, strength, and resilience of the people of Morgrim.
DescFinal=Firm as a rock. Thus are true workers forged. You have borne the weight of the earth, and she has accepted you. Take this recipe, son of the forge, and let your craft be as eternal as Morgrim's stone.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=28
PosMap=594

[QUEST285]
Nombre=Underground Antennas
Desc=I want you to go into the Anthill. Don't ask too many questions; I don't have the answers yet. The ants are changing... coordinating. I need you to get 60 Ant Antennae. I'll examine their structures, their signals... and I'll know if my suspicions are true. If there's a Queen down there... I don't want Ullathorpe to find out too late. Come back as soon as you have the antennae!
DescFinal=So... my fears were true. These antennae don't belong to ordinary ants. There's a pattern, a frequency... as if something is guiding them. You've done more than you can imagine, traveler. With this information, perhaps we can prepare... before she awakens. Take your reward. And keep this quiet.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=1
DescAudio=1113
DescFinalAudio=1114

[QUEST286]
Nombre=The Custody of the Frogians
Desc=The frogs of Frogian Cave fiercely protect a rare botanical ingredient: the Shadow Water Lily, a magical plant gland that blooms only in waters magically altered by the presence of arcane amphibious creatures. Its "heart" is a hardened, dark purple seed that beats faintly as if it possessed a life of its own. The ancient inhabitants of Forgat considered this ingredient a natural protector against disease and poison, but over time the Frogian frogs took over the cave and guarded it like a treasure. The presence of sorcerers among them caused the plant to mutate, and today, harvesting it without dying in the attempt has become nearly impossible. If you recover the precious heart, I can continue my herbal research.
DescFinal=By the roots of Milthas! You did it! I thought those creatures would have devoured you, but here you are... and with the Heart of the Shadow Lily in your hands. Look at it... it's still beating. You have no idea how valuable this is to my research. You've done extraordinary work, traveler. Here, you've earned this reward. And if you ever need a remedy... seek me out. I owe more than one to someone with your courage.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=16
PosMap=62

[QUEST287]
Nombre=Living force of the Forest
Desc=Many wonder why I live up here in this old Tree House. Years ago, this place belonged to an order of druids who could listen to the forest better than anyone. I was just an apprentice when the Dry Oak Wars broke out... and when it was all over, I was the only one of my order to return to these branches. I chose to stay. The tree accepted me, and I accepted the silence of its leaves. Over time, I made this home my laboratory, where I study the vitality of the forest's creatures and how their essence can strengthen arcane magic. Since then, adventurers from Arghal and beyond have come here seeking guidance... or power. And as long as the tree stands, I will be here to aid those who know how to respect the living force of the forest. If you have come seeking power, I can help you... but nothing worthwhile comes without effort. To enhance your Magic Dart, I need materials that only Piaras Forest can provide. Three creatures guard it: the Boar, the Wild Boar, and their fearsome leader, the Alpha Boar. It is not enough to face them: you must bring me two of their horns and the Alpha's pelt. Within them resides the wild essence I need to complete my spell. Go, prove your resolve... and when you return with all that I have asked for, I will transform your magic into something far more powerful. Desde então, aventureiros de Arghal e de outros lugares vieram aqui em busca de orientação... ou poder. E enquanto a árvore estiver de pé, estarei aqui para ajudar aqueles que souberem respeitar a força vital da floresta. Se você veio em busca de poder, posso ajudá-lo... mas nada que valha a pena vem sem esforço. Para aprimorar seu Dardo Mágico, preciso de materiais que somente a Floresta de Piaras pode fornecer. Três criaturas a guardam: o Javali, o Javali Selvagem e seu temível líder, o Javali Alfa. Não basta enfrentá-los: você deve me trazer dois de seus chifres e a pele do Alfa. Neles reside a essência selvagem que preciso para completar meu feitiço. Vá, prove sua determinação... e quando retornar com tudo o que pedi, transformarei sua magia em algo muito mais poderoso.
DescFinal=Ah... Perfect! These horns still hold the primal energy of the forest, and this fur... Yes, the essence of the Alpha is strong in it. You've done admirable work. Now observe. By blending the wild vitality with your own mana, I can refine your basic spell and grant you one worthy of a true, budding mage.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=4
PosMap=157

[QUEST288]
Nombre=Echoes of the Profane Forest
Desc=Come closer, my son... I see weariness in your eyes, but also courage. And that courage is precisely what I need to face a darkness that looms beyond these walls. Listen carefully, because what I'm about to tell you shouldn't be taken lightly. Outside the Castle lies a place that was once a living forest, a haven of peace where the wind played among the leaves and the earth breathed light. In its heart grew the sacred Araucaria de Semilla, a flower unique in all of Argentum, which, when it fell, gave life in the form of powerful Prosperous Seeds, essential for brewing the energy potions that sustain our warriors. But years ago... something profane touched that place. A dark force—the remnant of a sorcerer who defied the laws of life and death—became trapped in the forest like an open wound. Since then, the roots have become infected, the earth has cracked... and the dead have begun to rise. That forest no longer belongs to the living. Zombies patrol it like guardians of a curse they don't even understand. Their moans are nothing more than fragments of a forgotten incantation, endlessly repeating. And yet... the Araucaria endures. Wounded, yes, but clinging to its purpose. Each time it dies under the ravages of corruption, it is reborn and releases one last seed brimming with hope. Adventurer... I ask you to enter that forest. Confront the undead that infest it. Give them back the rest they were denied. And bring back some Prosperous Seeds of the Araucaria before its eternal cycle is finally broken.
DescFinal=By the gods... fifty Prosperous Seeds. I can't remember the last time someone returned with so many. The forest must have resisted your advance with fury, but you still prevailed. You have brought hope to this city, adventurer. These seeds will sustain our healers, our guardians, and perhaps... something more. I see that the echoes of the Unholy Forest failed to break you. That means you are ready to receive what I promised you. Ancient... and dangerous knowledge. Not everyone can bear this twisted blessing without being lost within it. From this moment on, you will be able to Summon Zombies. Not one of the damned of the forest, but a purified spirit, freed from the curse you yourself faced. It will not serve you out of ambition... but for balance. Remember that whoever controls a dead person also carries part of their history. Your work in the forest will not be forgotten. And if one day that place rises up against life again, I will know whom to call.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=8
PosMap=319

[QUEST289]
Nombre=Green Lesson
Desc=Você trilhou um caminho perigoso, aprendiz. De um lado ruge Penthar, onde orcs travam sua guerra sem compreender a magia que empunham. Do outro, a Montanha Perdida guarda os ecos de minotauros caídos, orgulhosos demais para morrer em silêncio. Entre eles, apodrece esta floresta... território goblin. Eles invadem meus círculos, roubam meus componentes e profanam meus rituais. Mas eu não os odeio: eu os estudo. Seu feitiço Invocar Zumbi é mera obediência à carne morta. Eu lhe ensinarei algo superior: dominar a vontade dos vivos. Vá para a Floresta Goblin. Derrote-os. Observe-os fugir, implorar e cair. Quando estiver suficientemente subjugado, retorne à minha cabana. Então, encarando Penthar e sob a sombra da Montanha Perdida, eu reescreverei sua magia.
DescFinal=Death obeys because it has no choice. The living obey because you break their will.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=12
PosMap=186

[QUEST290]
Nombre=The Roar that Clears the Way
Desc=This dock was once a resting place for merchants and fishermen traveling to Penthar. But something stirred the fury of the forest panthers... they no longer hunt for hunger, but for territory. My spells keep a few at bay, but the path is blocked. No one may pass. If you truly wish to strengthen your Wild Roar, prove to me that you can impose your will upon the beast. Go into the forest. Slay 15 panthers and restore calm to the path. When you return, if you are still standing, I will teach your magic to roar like never before.
DescFinal=Magic answers those who dare to face the beast and do not back down. From now on, your spell will no longer be a mere Arcane Roar.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=12
PosMap=247

[QUEST291]
Nombre=The Heartbeat of the Ancient Fire
Desc=Centuries ago, when dragons still ruled the skies, ancient mages sealed a formidable power deep within this dungeon. The Latent Fire, a primal power that not only burns but pulses, like the heart of an ancient dragon... Within that temple dwell the Pyrrak. Humanoid beings with red scales, like glowing embers, with eyes like burning coals. They are descended from dragons, but have abandoned their winged form to walk on two legs, like monsters of fire and fury. The Pyrrak are the guardians of that power. Their bodies glow with the heat of a thousand suns, and their fury knows no bounds. If you wish to attain the Fiery Heartbeat, you must first defeat them. 30 Pyrrak, I challenge you to destroy them within their lair in the Dragon Dungeon. Only then will the Fiery Radiance resonate within you, and you will be able to summon the Fiery Heartbeat. But beware, young sorcerer… This power is not a gift, it is a curse, and those who are not worthy will burn in their own flames.
DescFinal=I can see the marks of fire on your spirit. Those humanoid creatures with red scales do not die easily... and yet, thirty of them have fallen by your hand. The fire of the Dragon Dungeon has recognized you. You are no longer a mere wielder of the Blazing Flame... now its heart beats in time with yours.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=22
PosMap=30

[QUEST292]
Nombre=Burning Echoes of the Dead
Desc=Listen closely, traveler, for this story is never repeated. When the sun sets over Kamal and the tide recedes, the pyramid casts a shadow that points directly out to sea. This is no coincidence. It was erected to imprison that which should never rise again. Those we now call mummies were, in life, bearers of powerful magic. Upon death, their bodies were sealed with spells that still echo beneath the sand. This is why they walk... and why they guard the pyramid. Your Arcane Roar is strong, I know. You have tested it against living beasts. But within the pyramid, you will not face flesh and blood... you will face echoes. You must venture into its corridors, where the air burns and the silence weighs heavily. There, each mummy you defeat will release a fragment of ancient magic. When you have destroyed fifty, the roar will cease to be merely a voice. The sand will absorb the sound... and return it as fire. Only then will you return here. If you continue breathing, I will know that the pyramid has accepted you... and that your spell is ready to transform.
DescFinal=I don't need to ask you what you saw in there. The sand no longer clings to your shadow... and the air around you trembles. That only happens to those who have survived the trial at the pyramid. Fifty guardians of bandages and bone have fallen. With each one, an ancient voice was silenced... and another ignited within you. Listen now to your magic.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=18
PosMap=20

[QUEST293]
Nombre=The breath that forges Ice
Desc=The power born in the North Winds has begun to shift. The ice you learned to master no longer merely shatters; it now responds. The depths where the ancient fire burns hold a test the Threshold never attempted. There, magic manifests as breath, an exhalation capable of melting spells and wills alike. Forgotten texts warn that resisting this fire means not destroying it, but understanding it. Confront this source of power and subdue its fury. In doing so, the Glacial Fracture will evolve, taking on a new form born from the clash of cold and fire—a magic that breathes and expands like a contained breath.
DescFinal=The north gave you strength. Fire gave you its breath.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=31

[QUEST300]
Nombre=The Shared Magic of Christmas
Desc=Listen, adventurer... Christmas in Eleusis doesn't depend on just one person, but on everyone. Every time you give me 100 Christmas Cookies, you're increasing the community counter that keeps the magic of winter alive. But pay attention: when we've gathered enough cookies, a great threat from the cold will appear. Until that creature is defeated, no one can continue giving cookies. Our goal is enormous: we need to collect one million cookies from all the adventurers. The more people who help and the more cookies are given, the faster we'll reach the goal and unlock the path to unique rewards for this event.
DescFinal=Well done, adventurer! Your contribution is now part of the community tally. Every 100 cookies you bring takes us one step closer to our goal. The more everyone collaborates, the faster we'll progress. If you still have the energy, you can go out again, collect more cookies, and come back when you're ready to continue helping. The magic of Christmas lives on thanks to efforts like yours.
Repetible=1

[QUEST301]
Nombre=Christmas in danger
Desc=Listen up, adventurer... This Christmas Eve, creatures of winter have begun to roam outside Eleusis. Christmas elves, nutcrackers, and frostys infest the snowy roads and are disturbing the peace of the city. I need you to go out and defeat them. Each of these beings must be eliminated for winter to return to order. As they fall, they will leave behind Christmas Cookies, fragments of the magic that protects this holiday. Gather these cookies and contribute them to help the entire community of Eleusis keep Christmas alive. The more enemies we defeat together, the closer we will be to restoring the balance of winter. Return when you have completed your task, and I will ensure your efforts are rewarded.
DescFinal=Good work, adventurer. The creatures of winter have been contained, and Eleusis can breathe easy once more. Your efforts haven't gone unnoticed: each time you help protect Christmas, your experience grows, and your bag becomes heavier. If you still have the strength, you can go out again and repeat the task. The more times you help, the greater your experience and the more gold you'll earn. Christmas always needs heroes... and Eleusis will be waiting for you.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=10

[QUEST302]
Nombre=Christmas in danger
Desc=Listen up, adventurer... This Christmas Eve, creatures of winter have begun to roam outside Eleusis. Christmas elves, nutcrackers, and frostys infest the snowy roads and are disturbing the peace of the city. I need you to go out and defeat them. Each of these beings must be eliminated for winter to return to order. As they fall, they will leave behind Christmas Cookies, fragments of the magic that protects this holiday. Gather these cookies and contribute them to help the entire community of Eleusis keep Christmas alive. The more enemies we defeat together, the closer we will be to restoring the balance of winter. Return when you have completed your task, and I will ensure your efforts are rewarded.
DescFinal=Good work, adventurer. The creatures of winter have been contained, and Eleusis can breathe easy once more. Your efforts haven't gone unnoticed: each time you help protect Christmas, your experience grows, and your bag becomes heavier. If you still have the strength, you can go out again and repeat the task. The more times you help, the greater your experience and the more gold you'll earn. Christmas always needs heroes... and Eleusis will be waiting for you.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=20

[QUEST303]
Nombre=Christmas in danger
Desc=Listen up, adventurer... This Christmas Eve, creatures of winter have begun to roam outside Eleusis. Christmas elves, nutcrackers, and frostys infest the snowy roads and are disturbing the peace of the city. I need you to go out and defeat them. Each of these beings must be eliminated for winter to return to order. As they fall, they will leave behind Christmas Cookies, fragments of the magic that protects this holiday. Gather these cookies and contribute them to help the entire community of Eleusis keep Christmas alive. The more enemies we defeat together, the closer we will be to restoring the balance of winter. Return when you have completed your task, and I will ensure your efforts are rewarded.
DescFinal=Good work, adventurer. The creatures of winter have been contained, and Eleusis can breathe easy once more. Your efforts haven't gone unnoticed: each time you help protect Christmas, your experience grows, and your bag becomes heavier. If you still have the strength, you can go out again and repeat the task. The more times you help, the greater your experience and the more gold you'll earn. Christmas always needs heroes... and Eleusis will be waiting for you.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=30

[QUEST304]
Nombre=First Christmas Gift
Desc=As event participants contribute Christmas Cookies to this city's community counter, this Christmas's rewards will be unlocked. To receive this Christmas Gift, you must have at least one Christmas Star in your inventory and wait until the community has contributed a total of 50,000 Christmas Cookies.
Repetible=1

[QUEST305]
Nombre=Second Christmas Gift
Desc=As event participants contribute Christmas Cookies to this city's community counter, this Christmas's rewards will be unlocked. To receive this Christmas Gift, you must have a Christmas Star in your inventory and wait until the community has contributed a total of 100,000 Christmas Cookies.
Repetible=1

