Nombre=Eighth Christmas Gift
Desc=As event participants contribute Christmas Cookies to this city's community counter, this Christmas's rewards will be unlocked. To receive this Christmas Gift, you must have a Christmas Star in your inventory and wait until the community has contributed a total of 400,000 Christmas Cookies.
Repetible=1

[QUEST312]
Nombre=Last Christmas Gift
Desc=As event participants contribute Christmas Cookies to this city's community counter, this Christmas's rewards will be unlocked. To receive this Christmas Gift, you must have a Christmas Star in your inventory and wait until the community has contributed a total of 500,000 Christmas Cookies.
Repetible=1

[QUEST313]
Nombre=Christmas in danger
Desc=This is the final mission: Eliminate Krampus. If you do, claim these rewards!
Repetible=1

[QUEST314]
Nombre=Ashes of the First Fire
Desc=Listen carefully, stranger, for I will not repeat this. The Phoenix does not always leave behind the same thing upon dying. Most of the time, only ashes and a feather plucked in combat. But on rare occasions, very rare indeed, its fire condenses into something more. An Egg. I have witnessed hundreds of rebirths from this forge, and I swear by the lava of Morgrim that barely one in a hundred leaves a complete egg. If fate smiles upon you and the Phoenix drops one upon falling, consider yourself chosen. But not everyone entrusts their future to chance. Each feather you pluck from the Phoenix holds a fragment of its rebirth. One is not enough. Nor are two. Ten feathers... from ten different deaths... together they beat like a heart of fire. Bring me ten feathers, and I will do what chance did not: I will forge a Phoenix Egg with my own hands.
DescFinal=Ten feathers, still burning. Not all come from the same rebirth. That is good. Fire needs conflict to awaken. See how they tremble, the Egg already claims form. Take it. Remember this, Firebearer: the Phoenix always rises again... and now, its fire walks with you.
Repetible=1

[QUEST315]
Nombre=The Wings of Eternal Fire
Desc=I thought the fire would subside after the Egg... But no. The Phoenix has recognized you. Each time it falls and rises again, its wings grow stronger. They are not mere limbs... they are the symbol of its rebirth. To pluck a single feather is to defy its will. To pluck twenty... is to walk on its shadow. Listen carefully: one or ten feathers hold power, yes... but twenty feathers hold memory. The memory of every flight, every fall, every time the Phoenix chose to live again. With twenty feathers, I can forge something no dwarf has attempted since. Not true wings... but an echo of its own. Wings that will not lift you to the heavens, but will announce to all that you have survived the fire time and time again. Bring me twenty Phoenix feathers. And let the world know that the fire did not consume you.
DescFinal=Twenty feathers... Each one burned my fingers upon touching them. A good omen. See how the fire obeys... the wings remember how to burn. Take them. They won't give you flight, but they will give you presence. Wherever you walk, they will know that you defied the Phoenix twenty times... and still stand.
Repetible=1

[QUEST316]
Nombre=Christmas in danger
Desc=This is the final mission: Eliminate Krampus. If you do, claim these rewards!
Repetible=1

[QUEST317]
Nombre=The Echo of the Howls
Desc=It is not just a cave. It is a place where sanity is lost.  They call it the Cave of Desolation because everyone who enters feels something dark watching them. From its depths emerge creatures that are no longer men... but not beasts either. Ululantis, Ferus, and Laicans roam the tunnels, guided by a savage instinct that knows no rest. They were once guardians, hunters, travelers. Now only bodies twisted by the curse remain. Their howls echo through the night, and each day they draw closer to the roads that lead to the city. If we do nothing, soon there will be no safe corner left in this region. Enter the cave and eliminate as many as you can. Each creature defeated is one more life saved outside. When you have completed your task, return to me. I will reward you with gold and experience for facing the desolation that dwells in that place.
DescFinal=What you did was not just hunting beasts… it was stopping a tragedy. The presence in the cave has weakened, and for the first time in a long while, the air feels lighter. Ululantis, Ferus, and Laicans no longer dominate the tunnels as they once did. It is not a final victory, but it is a necessary one. Each creature you defeated delayed the advance of the curse and gave this land time to breathe. Take your reward. Rest, for facing desolation leaves its mark… and sooner or later, it will call again.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=16
PosMap=418

[QUEST318]
Nombre=The Clan of the Sands
Desc=This is no isolated group, it is an entire clan. A clan of kobolds has settled in the desert, near the pyramid and the oasis. They are organized by colors, each fulfilling a role within their structure. The greys scout and keep watch, the browns dig and fortify, the blues protect the water sources, and the reds form the attacking force. As long as they act as a clan, their presence will continue to grow. They are no longer simple wandering creatures: they are claiming territory and preparing for something greater. If we do not stop them now, they will soon dominate the area around the oasis, and no traveler will be able to cross the desert safely. Go and thin their ranks. Eliminate grey, brown, blue, and red kobolds. The color does not matter: every one that falls weakens the clan’s structure. Strike them before they finish consolidating their power. When you have done your part, return to me. I will reward you with gold and experience for helping prevent this clan from becoming an unstoppable threat.
DescFinal=Well done. The clan has felt the blow. It has not been destroyed, but its organization has been weakened and its advance has been slowed. Now they know they are not alone in this desert... and that someone is willing to stand against them. Take your reward. But stay alert. As long as that clan exists near the pyramid and the oasis, they will always seek a way to regain their strength.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=14
PosMap=16

[QUEST319]
Nombre=Contaminated energy
Desc=The swamp is alive and sick. Before the Mutant Colossus appeared, this area was dangerous, but stable. When that abomination emerged, something seeped into the earth and water. Then they came; we call them Miastrix. They didn't exist before. They are the result of the contamination left by the Colossus... creatures formed from twisted energy and swamp. Their bodies, their movements, the way they attack... everything about them responds to something we don't yet understand. I need you to eliminate 25 Miastrix, but also to observe: How do they react to combat? What does the earth do when they fall? What remains floating in the air afterward? With that information, I can condense the residual energy and create an Earth Core. I won't tell you why I'm giving it to you. I only know that the swamp responds differently when you are the one acting. And that... worries me as much as it intrigues me.
DescFinal=What you observed confirms my suspicions. The Miastrix don't move randomly. They respond to a pulse... something that remained anchored since the appearance of the Mutant Colossus. With what you brought, I was able to condense this. It's an Earthly Core. It shouldn't exist. And yet, it reacted when you thought of returning it to the swamp. That's why it's yours. Sell it if you want. Or give it to someone who knows how to listen to what it holds. Just... don't carry it around for too long.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=1
DescAudio=1117
DescFinalAudio=1118

[QUEST320]
Nombre=Anomalous Resonance
Desc=I see you've brought something exceptional. That Earthly Core shouldn't be in just anyone's hands. Its energy is both powerful and delicate. If you mishandle it, it could unleash consequences neither you nor I wish to see. I need you to give it to me. I promise I won't use it for anything other than studying it. I won't move it, sell it, or destroy it: I'll only examine it to understand its nature. In return, you'll receive a reward for your time and effort. But more importantly, your discretion ensures this power doesn't fall into the wrong hands.
DescFinal=Not everyone would be prudent enough to do that. Perhaps that makes you proud... or perhaps it leaves you wondering what else could have happened.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=34
DescAudio=1119
DescFinalAudio=1120

[QUEST321]
Nombre=The awakening of the Pyramid
Desc=This is no ordinary tomb. The pyramid has awakened once again. The desert sands are shifting, and with them, the creatures that lie beneath its walls. Giant scarabs crawl out from the cracks, smaller scarabs infest the corridors, and the mummies of ancient kings walk once more among the shadows. If we do not stop them now, the pyramid will become an uncontrollable nest. From there, the entire desert will be filled with wandering dead and corrupted beasts. We cannot allow that to happen. Enter the pyramid and eliminate as many as you can. Reduce their numbers before they organize. Every creature defeated is one more step toward keeping this place sealed. When you have completed your task, return to me. I will reward you with gold and experience for helping to keep the desert under control.
DescFinal=Well done. The pyramid is silent once again... for now. The advance of the creatures has been halted, and the sands rest once more. But do not let your guard down: as long as that place exists, something will always seek to escape. Take your reward. And if the pyramid stirs again, I will need your sword once more.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=18
PosMap=17
DescAudio=1121
DescFinalAudio=1122

[QUEST322]
Nombre=Purging the Forest of the Fallen
Desc=The Zombie Forests are no longer just cursed lands. They are now a direct threat to Banderbill and Nix. Patrols from both cities report that the dead are gathering far too close to the main roads. Alongside the already known Zombies, plague-corrupted dogs have appeared, mindless walkers, putrefied corpses that spread disease, and even ancient warriors who still carry their armor march endlessly among the trees. Each night they draw a little closer to the city walls. If we do not reduce their numbers now, soon there will be no way to contain them. Civilians, merchants, and supply routes will be exposed to constant attacks. Enter the Zombie Forest and eliminate as many as you can. Slow or fierce, they are all part of the same horde. Each creature destroyed is another chance for peace to remain standing. When you have completed your task, return to me. You will be rewarded with gold and experience for helping to keep the undead at bay.
DescFinal=What you did today gave the cities a moment to breathe. Patrols report that the pressure in the forest has eased and that the roads are once again passable, at least for now. The dead are still there, but their numbers are no longer as overwhelming as before. It is not a final victory, but it is a necessary one. Each zombie that fell to your weapon is one less threat to Banderbill and Nix, and one more hope for those who live behind their walls. Take your reward. The locals and merchants will not forget your help... and if the forest fills with shadows again, we will need you once more.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=58
DescAudio=1123
DescFinalAudio=1124

[QUEST323]
Nombre=The Call of the Beasts
Desc=Listen carefully, Hunter. The forest doesn't respond to words, it responds to deeds. Wargs run with the fury of the wind, and grizzly bears endure like the earth itself. If you cannot face both, they will never walk beside you. You must venture deep into the forest and slay 35 wargs and 20 grizzly bears. Not out of cruelty, but so that the spirits may see that you understand their nature. Among their remains, an ancient relic may appear... a Mystic Stone. It is brown like tree bark, with veins as white as bone. This stone is not common. It forms when a beast dies defending its territory. It holds the echo of its spirit. Bring it to me. If the forest deems you worthy, the stone will choose you... and I will know you are ready.
DescFinal=The stone holds the fury of the direwolf and the resilience of the bear. It does not submit... it answers back. From now on, when you call, they will come. The direwolf will run to your side with sharp fangs, and the grizzly bear will stand firm against your enemies. Use this power with respect, Hunter. The forest watches... and never forgets.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=13
PosMap=55
DescAudio=1125
DescFinalAudio=1126

[QUEST324]
Nombre=The Seal of Ancient Fury
Desc=You have ventured where few hunters dare. South of this Elven Forest lies Pirate Island. This place was torn from the forest by violence. The spirits abandoned it... but the beasts remained. The Dire Wolves that roam the island hunt without fear or rest. They learned to kill to dominate. The Ursids withstood the chaos. They are pure strength, flesh, and fury. By slaying these creatures, a relic of the island may appear: a Mystic Rune, etched with ancient symbols and marked by salt and blood. This rune does not belong to the forest. It is the mark of what survives when the balance is broken. Journey to Pirate Island. Slay Dire Wolves and Ursids until the rune chooses you. If you return with it, I will know you are ready to summon the beasts born of chaos.
DescFinal=So the island allowed you to return... This rune was carved when the forest lost its hold on this place. It does not invoke balance. It invokes survival. The Direwolf you summon will attack relentlessly, like those that rule these shores. The Ursidae will endure where others would fall, hardened by the fury of the south. From now on, you do not summon mere beasts. You summon the spirits born when the world shattered. Use this power wisely, Hunter. Even chaos remembers those who master it.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
PosMap=236
DescAudio=1127

[QUEST325]
Nombre=Ancient Fire Gems
Desc=I was young when I first heard this story, long before I opened my jewelry shop in this city. In those days, dragons weren't mere monsters to be hunted; they were part of the world, as ancient as magic itself. Each dragon is born bound to an element, and over the years that power condenses within. Blue Dragons fly where the cold cuts to the bone. Their breath freezes the air and the soul, and within them forms the Blue Stone, icy and silent. Red Dragons know only fury. They live among flames and ashes, and their rage never subsides. From them comes the Red Stone, hot even after the dragon's death. But Gold Dragons... they are different. They are few in number, and that is precisely why they are fearsome. They are guardians of ancient secrets, creatures who understand the value of gold better than any king. From them comes the Golden Stone, a gem capable of changing the destiny of its possessor. Listen carefully, adventurer... Don't ask why I need these stones. Nor why I'm willing to pay more gold than it's worth on any known market. There are jobs that shouldn't be done in public view, and powers that are best kept... contained.
DescFinal=Well done! Not just anyone makes it back from the Dragon Dungeon alive, let alone with these three gems intact. Here. More than I promised. These stones are worth it... and so is the risk. If you ever run into them again, you know where to bring anything that falls from their bodies.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=31
PosMap=78

[QUEST326]
Nombre=A special order
Desc=You must help me! King Tancred will be here in town soon and Governor Conrad has commissioned me to throw a great banquet for him and his troops... But I don't have enough fishermen to feed so many, much less a King! I know there is a special fish, the Bottom Grouper... it is elusive and can be a bit of work to get, but you should be able to catch it anywhere. If you manage to do it I will reward you, please help me!
DescFinal=You saved my neck! I will be eternally grateful. If you like to get more fish, talk to me again, there will always be hungry soldiers in Nix.
RequiredLevel=1
Repetible=1
PosMap=34

[QUEST327]
Nombre=The old Jacobo
Desc=Those damn goblins attacked my cart and stole my hooks. I'll never be able to train newbies without them! Recover them for me and show the world what it means to be a Great Angler. If you can do it, I promise to improve that old stick you call Fishing Rod with my fabulous old Jacobo technique.
DescFinal=That will teach those damn goblins not to mess with the fishing guild, excellent job!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=14
PosMap=34

[QUEST328]
Nombre=Mysterious Message
Desc=Have you managed to catch a mysterious bottle? Don't open it! I can offer you a great reward if you fulfill my fish order. Don't tell anyone about this!
DescFinal=If you ever catch a bottle again, don't hesitate to come back!
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=14
PosMap=254

[QUEST329]
Nombre=Beyond the Hook
Desc=Do you really think a Reinforced Rod is enough to brave the treacherous rivers of the North? True fishing requires precision, patience... and a worthy tool. My uncle taught me the essentials, but I've taken his techniques a step further. If you want an Iron Fishing Rod, I'll need special parts. Bring that Reinforced Rod and obtain a Claw of the Azhurion. With those materials, I will forge you a rod that will not only catch fish, but tame the most stubborn fish. Do you accept the challenge?
DescFinal=There you have it: the Iron Fishing Rod. Lightweight, durable, and with a reel that won't jam even if you catch a river beast. My uncle Jacobo would say that 'fishing is patience,' but I say it's also science. Go out there and show the water who's boss.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=20
PosMap=61

[QUEST330]
Nombre=Bronze Cup Exchange
Desc=You can trade your Bronze Cups for something better! If you have 5 Cups, I can exchange them for a Silver Cup.
Repetible=1
DescAudio=1074

[QUEST331]
Nombre=Silver Cup Exchange
Desc=You can trade your Silver Cups for something better! If you have 5 Cups, I can exchange them for a Gold Cup.
Repetible=1
DescAudio=1075

[QUEST332]
Nombre=Gold Cup Exchange
Desc=You can trade your Gold Cups for something better! If you have 5 Cups, I can exchange them for a Praetorian Tunic.
Repetible=1
DescAudio=1076

[QUEST333]
Nombre=Gold Cup Exchange
Desc=You can trade your Gold Cups for something better! If you have 5 Cups, I can exchange them for a Praetorian Tunic.
Repetible=1
DescAudio=1077

[QUEST334]
Nombre=Elemental Silks
Desc=I have dedicated much of my life to studying ancient arcane techniques capable of creating fabrics imbued with elemental energy. According to my research, the silks produced by the Elemental Spiders of the Catacombs possess unique properties when combined correctly. Ancient chronicles tell of how, using fibers from the four elements, it is possible to create an extremely light and strong thread. With this material, in ancient times, fabrics were woven that were linked to magical and legendary creatures. Among these legends appears the Unicorn... a mystical creature that only manifests itself to those who possess a special connection to elemental magic. If I wish to verify if these stories are true, I must first gather a vast quantity of elemental silks. That is why I need your help, adventurer. You must venture into the depths of the Catacombs and hunt the Elemental Spiders that dwell there. Each one produces a silk infused with the power of its element. Yes... I need one hundred of each. Only with that quantity will I be able to work properly with the energies of the four elements.
DescFinal=I see you've returned... and not empty-handed. Let me see those silks... Incredible. The elemental energy they contain is even purer than I expected. With an amount like this, I can finally begin my work at the loom. Weaving together the essences of water, fire, wind, and earth is no easy task, but if the ancient legends are true, this will be the first step toward creating a material worthy of the most magical creatures that have ever existed. You've done a great job, adventurer. Take this: it's Amida Light Thread. It's just the beginning of something much greater... and perhaps, if the stories are to be believed, also the first step toward the mystery of the Unicorn.
Repetible=1
PosMap=1
DescAudio=1046
DescFinalAudio=1047

[QUEST335]
Nombre=The Arcane Loom
Desc=Arkhavel has taken the first step by creating the Light Amida Thread, but now the real challenge begins. To weave a fabric capable of holding ancient magic, I must work for days at my arcane loom. However, to accomplish this, I need a vast quantity of this material. If you truly wish to continue this project, you must bring me a large supply of Light Amida Thread. Only with that amount can I attempt to weave something few have seen in centuries: a Unicorn Canvas.
DescFinal=This is... extraordinary. I never thought I'd see so many Lightweight Amida Yarns gathered in one place. Weaving this material hasn't been easy, but the result speaks for itself. Elemental energy flows through every fiber of the fabric. This is the Unicorn Canvas. According to ancient legends, fabrics like this were used in rituals to attract and bind creatures of magical purity. If the old tales are true... this canvas could be the key to encountering one of them.
Repetible=1
PosMap=151
DescAudio=1078
DescFinalAudio=1079

[QUEST336]
Nombre=Unicorn Bond
Desc=The Unicorn Canvas you wear is unique, woven with pure elemental energies and ancient techniques almost forgotten by mortals. According to legend, only those who have demonstrated patience, dedication, and respect for the world's magic can approach a Unicorn. This canvas is not merely a fabric; it is a conduit for the energy of these creatures, capable of attracting them and binding them to a worthy rider. If you wish to walk alongside a Unicorn and share its power, you must give it to me. In return, you will receive the Unicorn Mount, a noble and magical being that will answer your call.
DescFinal=Take good care of it, adventurer, for only those who honor the magic of the world can maintain its trust.
Repetible=1
PosMap=517
DescAudio=1080
DescFinalAudio=1081

[QUEST337]
Nombre=Unicorn Bond
Desc=The Unicorn Canvas you wear is unique, woven with pure elemental energies and ancient techniques almost forgotten by mortals. According to legend, only those who have demonstrated patience, dedication, and respect for the world's magic can approach a Unicorn. This canvas is not merely a fabric; it is a conduit for the energy of these creatures, capable of attracting them and binding them to a worthy rider. If you wish to walk alongside a Unicorn and share its power, you must give it to me. In return, you will receive the Unicorn Mount, a noble and magical being that will answer your call.
DescFinal=Take good care of it, adventurer, for only those who honor the magic of the world can maintain its trust.
Repetible=1
DescAudio=1082
DescFinalAudio=1083

