Repetible=1
DescAudio=1084
DescFinalAudio=1085

[QUEST339]
Nombre=The Flame of Heroism
Desc=Within the Temple of the Paladins lies an ancient ritual reserved only for those who demonstrate discipline, willpower, and mastery of combat: the Rite of Heroism. This rite is not a gift or an immediate blessing; it is a test. Centuries ago, the temple's sages discovered that certain creatures and plants of the world contain a natural essence capable of awakening a warrior's physical potential. Not just anyone can gather these components: they must be obtained through effort, combat, and determination. Only then does the ritual work.
DescFinal=The ritual is complete. Your will will be the spark.
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=25
DescAudio=1086
DescFinalAudio=1087

[QUEST340]
Nombre=The Islands Dispute
Desc=The islands of New Hope and the Elven Forest are no longer what they once were. Ancient forces have awakened, and with them, creatures that have lost all sense of reason. In the heart of the forest, the Elven Ent has been corrupted. Its fury distinguishes no friend from foe, and all who approach are attacked without mercy. Further afield, on the shores of New Hope, a colossal beast known as Gigantor has emerged. Its wake is marked by destruction, and its presence threatens to erase any attempt at control over the island. But you are not the only one who has been sent. Soldiers from both factions march to these lands with the same objective: to prevail, to dominate the region... and to claim glory. Your mission is clear. Head to one of the contested islands. Hold your position. Defend the territory from those who would seize it... and when the time comes, confront the creature that dwells there. It will not be easy. These entities resurface over time, as if the land itself refuses to let them disappear. If you manage to defeat them and prove your loyalty in battle, you will be rewarded with a Potion of Factional Honor, proof of your courage and commitment. Remember this, soldier: here you don't just fight monsters... you fight for the honor of your faction. And only those who stand firm will be remembered.
DescFinal=The banners of your faction fly higher than ever. Your victory has not gone unnoticed. Messengers already carry news of your feat, and your name begins to resonate among your people as a symbol of determination and loyalty. You have proven that, even in contested territories, your will is stronger than any threat. In recognition, you receive a Potion of Factional Honor.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=25

[QUEST341]
Nombre=Subjugate the Warrior
Desc=You have tamed beasts and lesser creatures, but orcs are another story. They do not bend easily: their will is tempered in war, blood, and endurance. If you aspire to summon them, you must prove that your magic can prevail even over that which scorns submission. Venture into their domain, confront them without hesitation, and break their spirit. Only when you have subdued enough, return to me.
DescFinal=Might prevails where reason cannot!
Repetible=0
RequiredLevel=16
PosMap=69

[QUEST342]
Nombre=The Echo of the Howls
Desc=It is not just a cave. It is a place where sanity is lost.  They call it the Cave of Desolation because everyone who enters feels something dark watching them. From its depths emerge creatures that are no longer men... but not beasts either. Ululantis, Ferus, and Laicans roam the tunnels, guided by a savage instinct that knows no rest. They were once guardians, hunters, travelers. Now only bodies twisted by the curse remain. Their howls echo through the night, and each day they draw closer to the roads that lead to the city. If we do nothing, soon there will be no safe corner left in this region. Enter the cave and eliminate as many as you can. Each creature defeated is one more life saved outside. When you have completed your task, return to me. I will reward you with gold and experience for facing the desolation that dwells in that place.
DescFinal=What you did was not just hunting beasts… it was stopping a tragedy. The presence in the cave has weakened, and for the first time in a long while, the air feels lighter. Ululantis, Ferus, and Laicans no longer dominate the tunnels as they once did. It is not a final victory, but it is a necessary one. Each creature you defeated delayed the advance of the curse and gave this land time to breathe. Take your reward. Rest, for facing desolation leaves its mark… and sooner or later, it will call again.
Repetible=1
RequiredLevel=16
PosMap=418

[QUEST343]
Nombre=Quest solo armada
Desc=Si eres capaz de obtener 5000 Leñas y 5000 Leñas Élficas, podré darte una buena recompensa.
DescFinal=Excelente, ten un poco de experiencia para mejorar tu camino, vuelve a hablarme si quieres progresar aun más.
